Combat Fury 3<br>
Flurry 3<br>
Fury of the Ages 3<br>
Punishing Blade 3<br>
Double Riposte 2<br>
Ferocity 2<br>
Raging Flurry 2<br>
TM 2<br>
<br>
In answer to your question and I hope this helps.<br>
<br>
Fury of the Ages 3<br>
PB 3<br>
Flurry 3<br>
Ferocity 3<br>
<br>
Between those 4 you can prolly increase another damage another 35% or better by level 65 but as another person has posted &quot;we are using high end weapons and high end haste besides full offensive AA skills&quot;.<br>
<br>
and for that extra 25+ more in damage easily get that by attaining the above by level 65.<br>
<br>
I had FOA 3, Flurry 3, CF 3, Ferocity 2, Raging Flurry 2 and PB 2.  At level 65 when<br>
I hit PB 3 I saw an increase around 12-15% in damage done over a period of time.<br>
<br>
You will notice that when training most any offensive AA skill that the following usually happens:<br>
Training 1:  A bit more Damage (about 2%)<br>
Trainng 2: Improves another 2.5%-3%<br>
Training 3: Improves another 6%-15% more damage.<br>
<br>
The above varied percentages also depend on what offensive AA skills you are training in ie. the biggest increase I have ever seen was training in pb3.   <br>
<br>
So far I have seen this pattern in most AA skills like PB 3, Ferocity 3 etc.  When you finish that 3rd training all that time invested is worth it.  A lot of people get discouraged and stop after training 2 because they say &quot;is this all I improved&quot;.  Wait and see the best results after training 3 in most all offensive skills.  You will be happy you did.<br>
<br>
Bahh...and when I had pb 2 only one thing out aggroed me in a group.  A ranger with pb 3..can you say ouch.  Hmm..He doesn't anymore though.<br>
<br>
And its sooooo true about PoP Mobs.  Great exp or knock off 2-4 AA in one day and yes we can do great damage due to the type of mobs in PoV as an example.<br>
<br>
